==English==
===Etymology===
''[[perish]]'' + ''[[-eth]]'', the archaic third-person singular present tense suffix

===Verb form===
'''perisheth'''
# {{archaic}} [[third-person singular]] form of ''to [[honour]]''.
#:''These are but gauds: nay, what are lips?''
#:''Coral beneath the ocean-stream''
